# Full Context — my-server

## What this machine is
Production web server running the main API for example.com. PostgreSQL handles all persistent data. Redis for sessions and job queue. nginx as reverse proxy. Deployed via PM2.

## Architecture
```
internet → nginx (:80/:443) → node API (:3000) → PostgreSQL (:5432)
                                               → Redis (:6379)
```

## Key Paths
/opt/app/              — application code (git repo, branch: main)
/opt/app/.env          — production environment variables
/var/lib/postgresql/   — database files (DO NOT TOUCH directly)
/etc/nginx/            — nginx config
/home/deploy/logs/     — application logs
/home/deploy/backups/  — database backups (nightly cron)

## Running Services
| Service    | Command       | Port | Managed by |
|------------|---------------|------|------------|
| Node API   | pm2           | 3000 | PM2        |
| PostgreSQL | systemd       | 5432 | systemd    |
| Redis      | systemd       | 6379 | systemd    |
| nginx      | systemd       | 80   | systemd    |

## Health Checks
```bash
pm2 status                          # API process
systemctl status postgresql redis   # database/cache
curl -s http://localhost:3000/health # API health endpoint
```

## Database
PostgreSQL 15. Main database: `appdb`. Key tables: users, sessions, jobs.
Backup: /home/deploy/backups/appdb_YYYYMMDD.sql.gz (nightly at 2am)
Connection: psql -U deploy appdb

## Credentials / Secrets
See /opt/app/.env — do not share outside this machine.

## Known Issues
- Redis occasionally OOMs under heavy load — check with `redis-cli info memory`
- PM2 sometimes needs restart after kernel updates: `pm2 restart all`

## Deployment
```bash
cd /opt/app
git pull origin main
npm install --production
pm2 restart app
```

